FOS_HOW_DO_I_LOG_DAILY_ACTIVITY.string_value: How do I log my daily activity?

FOS_HOW_DO_I_LOG.string_value: How do I Log in to the application?

FOS_CLICK_ON_THE_DROPDOWN.string_value: Click on the dropdown 'Email ID' option to select Email ID, Phone No., Emp ID etc. as a login option. Enter Company name in case 'Emp ID' is selected as an option. Finally, enter the password to log in.

FOS_IF_PLEASE_CONTACT_YOUR.string_value: If 'Please contact your admin' is displayed while logging in, contact your supervisor for approval.

FOS_HOW_DO_I_RESET.string_value: How do I reset my password?

FOS_CLICK_ON_FORGET_PASSWORD'.string_value: Click on 'Forget Password' to change your password. Enter email ID to receive OTP.

FOS_HOW_DO_I_SEE.string_value: How do I see the history of deposits and closed visits?

FOS_SEE_LOANS_ALLOCATED_IN.string_value: See loans allocated in different months by clicking on the Month filter at the top right of the Portfolio section page.

FOS_HOW_TO_VISUALIZE_MY.string_value: How to visualize my collection performance?

FOS_APPLICATION_USER_CAN_VIEW_HISTORY.string_value: Application user can view history of visits done and deposits made by accessing 'History' section on left side menu.

FOS_HOW_TO_CREATE_VISITS.string_value: How to create visits for multiple loan accounts in Bulk?

FOS_SELECT_MULTIPLE_APPLICANT_ID.string_value: Select Multiple Applicant's ID on Portfolio Page for which visits to be scheduled. Click the ' + ' icon on the bottom right to schedule bulk surprise visits.

FOS_HOW_TO_CREATE_A.string_value: How to create a new visit for any loan account?

FOS_THERE_ARE_MULTIPLE_WAYS.string_value:
There are multiple ways to create a visit for an applicant: 
1. By utilizing Bulk visit option 
2. By Clicking on Applicant on Portfolio Page, then click the ' + ' icon on the bottom right of the Customer details page. 
3. Clicking on the 'Quick Visit' option on the customer details page.

FOS_PTP_VISIT_IS_SCHEDULED.string_value: PTP (Promise to Pay) visit is scheduled when the borrower promises to pay at a future date or time. FOS application user has to schedule a PTP for that applicant to call back or visit at provided date or time. A field Visit is a Surprise visit on a specific date/time when an applicant user visits an applicant first time.

FOS_WHATS_THE_DIFFERENCE_BETWEEN.string_value: What's the difference between a PTP visit and a field visit?

FOS_WHAT_IS_A_COLLECTION.string_value: What is a Collection Receipt and how to share receipts with the applicants?

FOS_COLLECTION_RECEIPT_PROVIDES_DETAILS.string_value: Collection receipt provides details to borrower regarding their payment to field agents. Field Agents can share receipts to borrowers by visiting 'History' section on left side menu.

FOS_HOW_TO_I_DEPOSIT.string_value: How to i deposit collected amount in company's account?

FOS_COLLECTED_AMOUNT_VIA_CASH.string_value: Collected amount via 'cash' or ' cheque' method can be deposited in a bank branch/company branch as per details provided by the company. To perform a deposit user needs to go to the "Collection" section and select applicable collections to perform the deposit.

FOS_TO_CONTINUE_GIVE_MEDIA_PERMISSION.string_value: To continue,give media permission to the app from settings-> apps -> fos -> permissions -> media.

FOS_TO_CONTINUE_GIVE_CAMERA_PERMISSION.string_value: To continue,give camera permission to the app from settings-> apps -> fos -> permissions -> camera.

FOS_MARK_YOUR_ATTENDANCE.string_value: Mark your attendance by utilizing Clock-in and Clock-out features on Home Page. After logging in, make sure to hit the "Clock-in" button on the top navigation bar when you are starting your day's work, and move the button to "clock-out" once you end your day. This keeps the daily activity logged.

FOS_DIFF_BTW_ADDRESS_MARKED_LOCATION.string_value: What's the difference between 'Address' and 'Markedlocation' for a visit?

FOS_ADDRESS_LAT_LONG_AT.string_value: Address / Lat-Long at top of the visit submission form refers to the applicant's location. Marked location is of an agent which is captured during submission of field visit.
